To solve the `ofExpression_correct` theorem, we need to prove that if an `Expression p` can be converted to an `AffineExpression p` (denoted as `some ae = AffineExpression.ofExpression? p e`), then the evaluation of this `AffineExpression p` (`ae.eval`) is equal to the evaluation of the original `Expression p` (`e.eval`).

